  "title": "Bangs, Bobs & Banter: Confessions of a Hairstylist",
  "description": "Watch Nikki juggle a cast of colourful clientele that come through her salon, confessing their saucy, sassy and scandalous hair-raising secrets, in this one-woman comedy! \"impressively polished...Rannelli is a winning performer\" (Orlando Weekly) \"Best Solo Show-Comedy\" (Orlando Fringe) \"Sold-Out Run\" (Edmonton Fringe 2024)",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Joanna Rannelli<br><strong>Director</strong>: Kerry Ipema<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Joanna Rannelli<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Muhammad Dewji<br/></br>",
  "website": "https://gravitytheatre.ca",
  "plain_language": "\"Bangs, Bobs &amp; Banter: Confessions of a Hairstylist\" is a one-woman show based on real-life stories. In the show, Joanna brings ten different characters to life, switching between them using wigs and music. The performance is lively and playful, much like the comedy sketches of Carol Burnett, mixing humour, heart, and a touch of drama as it explores the world inside a hair salon.",
